    "Hunan":  {
                  "dish":  "Mao Shi Hong Shao Rou (Mao\u0027s Red Braised Pork)",
                  "description":  "Named after Chairman Mao Zedong, a Hunan native who famously loved this dish. Unlike other braised pork recipes, the Hunan style traditionally uses caramelized sugar rather than soy sauce for its deep red color. Hunan cuisine, or Xiang cuisine, is known for its \u0027gan la\u0027 (dry heat) and use of fresh chilies, garlic, and shallots. This dish balances savory, sweet, and spicy notes with melt-in-your-mouth pork belly.",
